      "job_description": "JOB SUMMARY\nDesigns products and features that directly impact the consumer experience. Designs innovative solutions by collaborating with all involved teams and supporting new and existing features across multiple applications. Involved in reviewing and creating innovative solutions. Considered a subject matter expert for a single program/system.\n\nMAJOR DUTIES AND RESPONSIBILITIES\n• Actively and consistently supports all efforts to simplify and enhance the customer experience.\n• Design mockups to support product requirements.\n• Bring proven knowledge of user-centered design (UCD) process methods to digital applications from concept to launch.\n• Design information architecture and wireframes that both meet business goals and ensure a positive user experience.\n• Bring proven knowledge of new design techniques.\n• Partner with the wider design team to drive cross-platform consistency.\n• Modify, enhance, and implement design specifications and assets suitable for implementation.\n• Organize files and follows all established design patterns when applicable.\n• Responsible for design and wireframe reviews and brainstorming sessions to help solve problems.\n• Work within cross-functional team to understand expectations, priorities, and necessary deliverables.\n• Lead the greater design team to respond, clarify or define specific application look and feel.\n\nREQUIRED QUALIFICATIONS\nRequired Skills/Abilities and Knowledge\n• Ability to read, write, speak and understand English\n• Ability to demonstrate UI and UX design skills via portfolio\n• In-depth understanding of platform specific nomenclature\n• Experience with creating highly-detailed annotated wireframes, user flows, and process flows within consumer applications\n• Ability to sketch and generate big-picture ideas for early-stage UX work\n• Demonstrates effective time management skills and the ability to be self-directed when needed\n• Demonstrates effective client (presentation) communication skills and the ability to present and sell ideas to various audiences (technical and non-technical)\n• In-depth understanding of UX best practices\n• Demonstrated ability to deliver against several initiatives simultaneously\n• Ability to prioritize and organize effectively\n• Ability to fully engage and collaborate with team\n\nRequired Education\n• Bachelor's Degree in Design/Art/HCI/Media/Related Field, or equivalent real world experience\n• Required Related Work Experience and Number of Years\n• Digital design experience - 5+\n• Experience with basic prototyping tools (Invision, Flinto, Marvel, etc.) - 2\n• Experience with common Interface Tools (Axure, Omnigraffle, Balsamiq, Adobe Photoshop, Adobe Illustrator, Figma) - 2\n• Experience with project estimation\n• Experience with planning and facilitating user research and usability tests\n\nWORKING CONDITIONS\nOffice environment\n\nEOE\nCharter Communications is an Equal Opportunity Employer - Minority/Female/Veteran/Disability\nMPD322 332877 332877BR\n\nHere, employees don't just have jobs, they build careers. That's why we believe in offering a comprehensive package that rewards employees for their contributions to our success, supports all aspects of their well-being, and delivers real value at every stage of life.\n\nThe pay for this position has a salary range of $88,200.00 to $156,600.00. The actual salary offer will carefully consider a wide range of factors, including your skills, qualifications, experience and location. Also, certain positions are eligible for additional forms of compensation such as bonuses.",
